				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<p class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Don’t change your app every month</p>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-da1a8b8 desc_blog-post wavo-transform transform-type-translate elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="da1a8b8" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<p class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Redesigning constantly doesn’t make your product better. It makes it harder to use and easier to forget. In many startups, there’s an unsettling ritual: every month brings a redesign, a new feature set, or a completely reinvented flow.</p>				</div>
